# Angular App Conventions

## Stack

- Angular 22, standalone components (do not set `standalone: true` — it's default)
- Signals for state, `computed()` for derived values, `OnPush` change detection
- `inject()` instead of constructor injection
- `input()` / `output()` instead of decorators
- Native control flow: `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` — no `*ngIf` / `*ngFor`
- No `ngClass` / `ngStyle` — use `class` / `style` bindings

## Forms

Use **Signal Forms only** — see [Angular Signal Forms overview](https://angular.dev/guide/forms/signals/overview).

- Import from `@angular/forms/signals`: `form()`, `FormField`, schema validators (`required`, `min`, `max`, etc.)
- Bind inputs with `[formField]="myForm.fieldName"`; import `FormField` in the component
- **Do not use** `FormsModule`, `ngModel`, `ReactiveFormsModule`, `FormGroup`, `FormControl`, `FormArray`, or `formControlName`
- **Local UI filters:** use a local `signal` model + `form()` (e.g. `searchModel = signal({ query: '' })`)
- **Store-backed editing:** bridge with `linkedSignal` + `effect()` → store setters; never bind `form()` directly to `store.character` (ImprovementManager holds a mutable character reference)

## Structure

```
src/app/
  core/           # models, services, rules engine, utils
  features/       # routed feature areas (home, reference, characters, creation)
```

## Data loading

- Game data via `ChummerDataService` — HTTP from `/data/*.json`, cached
- Use `collection-utils.extractCollection()` for nested JSON wrappers
- Book codes resolved via `BookRegistryService`

## Rules integration

- UI calls `RulesEngineService` — never put bonus/BP logic in components
- Rules core lives in `src/app/core/rules/` and must stay framework-agnostic

## Accessibility

- WCAG AA: skip links, table captions, `aria-live` on search counts, focus styles
- Prefer semantic HTML (`nav`, `main`, `th scope="row"`)

## Scope discipline

- Match existing patterns in neighboring files
- Do not expand scope to unrelated features or refactors
